    <h3>Why Glucose Is Toxic in Your Blood</h3>
    <p>Glucose in the bloodstream is actually toxic. It glycates (damages) everything it touches:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Blood vessel walls become stiff</li>
        <li>Hemoglobin can't carry oxygen properly</li>
        <li>Enzymes stop working</li>
        <li>Hormones become dysfunctional</li>
        <li>Premature aging accelerates</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>The Body's Emergency Response</h3>
    <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
            <strong>You eat carbs/sugar</strong>
            <p>Glucose floods bloodstream within minutes</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
            <strong>Pancreas panics</strong>
            <p>Pumps insulin to force glucose out of blood</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
            <strong>Insulin pushes glucose into cells</strong>
            <p>Liver, muscles, fat cells - anywhere to get it out</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
            <strong>You eat again in 2-3 hours</strong>
            <p>Insulin never gets a chance to drop</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

